text: Theresa Ulmer (born February 26, 1962) was a member of the Arizona House of Representatives for a single term. She represented the 24th District during the 48th Legislature, winning the November 2006 election. She lost to Russell Jones during the general election during her unsuccessful re-election bid in 2008. ==References== Category:Arizona Democrats Category:Members of the Arizona House of Representatives Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:21st-century American politicians Category:21st-century American women politicians
